The Situation Room
Live from Washington
Tuesday, April 10, 2007

IN POLITICS:
•	Pres. Bush: Will Meet with Leaders of Both Parties on Military Funding
•	House Committee to Examine Pentagon's Tillman, Lynch Stories
•	House Panel Issues Subpoena for Justice Dept. Documents

IN THE NEWS:
•	More than 30 Killed in Bombings, Mortar Fire, Raids in Iraq
•	Rutgers Basketball Women Agree to Meet with Don Imus

IN THE CAFFERTY FILE:
•	Does Congress deserve to have its highest approval rating in a year?
•	Is it a good idea to penalize drivers who buy gas-guzzling vehicles?
•	Why has the number of morbidly obese Americans shot up dramatically in five years?

